               <scopecontent id="aspace_7a013f59091e3d02a37db45f47c977b4">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Term paper (1930), on the poet and musician who became the subject of Kastendieck's dissertation (1932).</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="aspace_s3b5f19.d0e1320" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Correspondence</unittitle>
                  <unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" unitdatetype="inclusive">1932-1938</unitdate>
                  <container containerid="39002119359983"
                             id="d1e931"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">5</container>
                  <container id="d1e933" localtype="folder" parent="d1e931">19</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_b97a7cba1f0d2ec81f7e925e301157cd">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>This correspondence concerns Kastendieck's efforts to publish his dissertation. It was eventually published by Oxford University Press in 1938 under the title <emph render="italic">England's Musical Poet: Thomas Campion</emph>.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
